Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%grams} into thirds, cutting any thick stems lengthways.

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%grams} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.25%tsp} for the noodles.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} and broccoli to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

While the noodles cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} to the pan and fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the @sliced mushrooms{120%grams} and pepper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir-fry until the chicken is cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Stir in the @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%grams} and cook for ~{1%min} more.

Add the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @bulgogi sauce{100%grams}, and @water{50%ml} for the sauce to the pan.

Stir to combine and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the cooked noodles and a good squeeze of lime juice from a lime wedge to the pan. Toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1%min}.

When ready, share your chicken stir-fry between your #serving bowls{}.

Scatter over the peanuts and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!